definitions.definition: a cup or other decorative object awarded as a prize for a victory or success.
examples: cup, medal; Moreprize, award "a swimming trophy"Moreprize, award a swimming trophy

definitions.definition: a souvenir of an achievement, especially a part of an animal taken when hunting.
examples: souvenir, memento, keepsake; Morespoils, booty "a cabinet full of trophies from his travels"Morespoils, booty a cabinet full of trophies from his travels

definitions.definition: (in ancient Greece or Rome) the weapons and other spoils of a defeated army set up as a memorial of victory.
a representation of a memorial of victory; an ornamental group of symbolic objects arranged for display.
in nouns corresponding to adjectives ending in -trophic (such as phototrophy corresponding to phototrophic ).
